Commentary Text: Bumrah to Hooda, out Caught by Pollard!! This is brilliant death bowling by Bumrah. A number of dot balls and now he gets rid of Hooda, who could have been dangerous. Was a full length delivery on off at 141 clicks and Hooda lofts it towards wide long-off. It's a skier and Pollard in the deep completes a safe reverse cup. Not the kind of end Punjab were looking for. Hooda c Pollard b Bumrah 28(26) [4s-1 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Shami to de Kock, out Bowled!! How's that for a comeback? Too good from Shami. Bowls with an upright seam, gets the ball to wobble in the air and it deviates ever so slightly to beat the laden-feet pull from QDK. Nothing slow about this from Shami, just landed the ball at the desired length and the his magic took care of the rest. In fact QDK got a tiny inside edge and lack of feet movement can be cited as a major reason for that. de Kock b Shami 27(29) [4s-2]
